  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nAllow the `address` constant to be passed as size when defining an array.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nCurrently vyper allows the use of two kinds of arrays:\r\n\r\nbyte arrays:\r\n`example_bytes: bytes[100] = b\"\\x01\\x02\\x03\"`\r\n\r\nstring arrays:\r\n`example_str: string[100] = \"Test String\"`\r\n\r\nFor some contracts it would be nice to be able to pass an array of addresses as an argument\r\nExample from the ERC777 standard:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef __init__(_name: string[32],\r\n             _symbol: string[16],\r\n             _totalSupply: uint256,\r\n             _granularity: uint256,\r\n             _defaultOperators: bytes[address]=\"\"\r\n            ):\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
