    "body": "I think we can already do this, an array of addresses would be defined as:\r\n```\r\n_defaultOperators: address[5]\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich just means: it can take an array of addresses in an array up until 5 slots.\r\nCan also be defined with literals\r\n```\r\ndefaultOperators: address[2] = [0x....0, adr1]\r\n```\r\nWithin a function. See the wallet example https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/examples/wallet/wallet.vy#L13",
